subject: Football
College Athletics
lead_paragraph: Damaris Johnson broke loose for a career-high 326 all-purpose yards to set an N.C.A.A. career record, and Tulsa took advantage of six first-half turnovers to beat No. 24 Hawaii, 62-35, in the Hawaii Bowl.
